value.0: Put anything you want to sell in this box.

1. Let the trader deal with these items.
This doesn't do anything (it's the same as 'Exit'). The merchant will negotiate a fair price with you himself. This also allows him to store the items he buys from you.

2. <CUSTOM5101>Sell all the items in the box.</CUSTOM5100>
You automatically sell all items currently in the box. The merchant gets a percentage and the items are taken out of the game. Look at the description of the chest for valid items and the price you'll get for them. 

3. Evaluate the items in the box.
Alternatively you can ask the merchant to present you a list of the items in the chest with their prices by clicking 'Evaluate Contents'.

1. Save chest's contents into slot(s).
This analyses the contents of the box' inventory and tries to assign the items to empty slots. If it finds the same item in any slot it will stack that slot. In short: you can store 15 different types of items, and each slot can contain multiple copies. You will get a warning if you want to store too many types of items.

2. Restore item(s) from slots.
With this option you can take items out of your slots again. They will appear in your inventory.

3. Sell item(s) to the system
You automatically sell all items in the selected slot. You get the item's worth and a percentage based on your merchant rank. The items are taken out of the game. Look at the description of the chest for valid items and the price you'll get for them.
